# Task Completion — Project Memory

**After finishing ANY task** (feature, bug fix, article, refactor, config change, skill install, etc.), update the relevant files in **`docs/project_notes/`** (see [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) «Система project memory»).

## What to Update

Pick the files that apply — not every task touches all four.

### `docs/project_notes/issues.md` — Work Log
Update **after every task**, no exceptions.
- Add a dated entry with a brief description of what was done
- Include the branch name, PR link, or issue URL if available
- Mark status (Completed / In Progress / Blocked)

### `docs/project_notes/bugs.md` — Bug Log
Update when **a bug was encountered and fixed** during the task.
- Document the issue, root cause, solution, and prevention
- Even small gotchas are worth recording if they took time to figure out

### `docs/project_notes/decisions.md` — Architectural Decisions
Update when **a non-trivial choice was made** (library selection, pattern change, config strategy, etc.).
- Add an ADR entry with context, decision, alternatives, and consequences
- Number sequentially (check existing entries for the next ADR number)

### `docs/project_notes/key_facts.md` — Project Configuration
Update when **project configuration, URLs, paths, ports, or tooling changed**.
- Keep it non-sensitive (no passwords, no API keys — those go in `.env`)
- Add new tools, services, important URLs, or environment details

## Checklist (run mentally before closing a task)

1. Did I log this work in `issues.md`?
2. Did I hit any bugs worth documenting in `bugs.md`?
3. Did I make an architectural or tooling decision → `decisions.md`?
4. Did project config/paths/URLs change → `key_facts.md`?

## Style Rules

- **Bullet lists** over tables
- **Concise entries** — 1-3 lines per item
- **Always dated** — use `YYYY-MM-DD`
- **Include URLs** — PRs, issues, docs, dashboards
- **Newest first** — add entries at the top of the log section

## Before Proposing Changes

- Check `decisions.md` before suggesting architectural changes
- Search `bugs.md` when encountering errors that feel familiar
- Consult `key_facts.md` for project configuration instead of guessing
